            16 => 
            array (
                'id' => 17,
                'name' => 'CRA-B27 CR2700 Battery',
            'description' => '<p>This battery features a built-in power gauge that shows battery power status intuitively every time the reader is triggered to scan or the power gauge button is pressed. &nbsp;A nurse will never need to guess whether the battery will last through her shift.&nbsp; &nbsp;When the battery is running low, a quick-release latch allows easy swapping for a fully charged battery without the need to use any tools.&nbsp; To proactively manage the life-cycle of the battery, the B27 accepts a custom date code to track deployment date or warranty service date that can be retrieved easily.&nbsp; In addition, battery health information is available to device or asset managers to track residual battery capacity.</p><p>The B27 battery can be charged when installed in a CR2700 reader using the inductive charging station (CRA-A271) or in the quad-bay battery charger (CRA-A274).&nbsp; It takes about 3.5-4 hours to fully charge a drained battery.</p>',
