            43 => 
            array (
                'id' => 44,
                'name' => 'CRA-271 CR2700 Bluetooth Charging Station',
                'description' => '<p>The A271 Bluetooth Inductive Charging Station fulfills two main functionalities for the CR2700 readers.&nbsp; First, it charges the battery in a CR2700 reader when the reader is placed in the charger, drawing power from a standard USB port on a host PC without the need for an external power supply.&nbsp; Second, it acts as a bridge for wireless communication between a CR2700 reader and a PC host.&nbsp; It features a sleek design that eliminates all exposed metal parts and associated contact failures caused by disinfectant use.&nbsp; A touch capacitive paging button helps the user to locate a misplaced reader easily and abolishes the crevices around a mechanical button.&nbsp; It now can withstand the harshest disinfectants commonly used at hospitals, making wiping down the device truly a breeze.&nbsp; Its unique form factor is compatible with both the palm and handle CR2700 readers and with multiple mounting accessories, streamlining device management requirements and minimizing maintenance costs.&nbsp; It is compatible with the CRA-C34 USB charging cable.</p>',
