            102 => 
            array (
                'id' => 103,
                'name' => 'Code Reader 4400',
                'description' => '<p>The CR4300 takes the camera from an iPod® or iPhone® and combines it with a patented optical platform and world-class decoding software to create a user-friendly,<br>high-performance barcode reader. The intuitive targeting bar and built-in left/right scan buttons provide a familiar interface for users to easily “point and shoot” their way through reading the toughest 1D and 2D barcodes.</p><p>Also coming in a non-scanning version the <strong>CR4300N</strong> combines ruggedness and extended power capabilities in a compact design. Built with industry-leading CodeShield® Disinfectant-Ready plastics, the CR4300N was designed to outperform and outlast consumer grade cases by standing up to the harshest of chemical agents and surviving multiple drops.</p><p>Both variations feature a 3000 mAh battery backup keeps your workforce running continuously. Each battery has a built-in battery gauge that informs users of battery status, simplifying workflows and keeping users in control. Code’s A160&nbsp; quad-bay enterprise charger can simultaneously charge 4 sleds, and the iOS devices they protect, in under 5 hours. Simply drop a depleted sled into the charger and grab a fully charged device to keep your business moving.</p><h2><strong>How do our customers use the CR4300/CR4300N?</strong></h2><p>The scanning CR4300 thrives in a manufacturing or retail setting. We see this reader used a lot for inventory, line-busting, field services, point-of-sale, ticketing, mobile coupons, and many more. The CR4300N is perfect for the mobile clinician that wan’t to protect their mobile device and keep it running longer.</p><p>Ready to purchase Code barcode readers for your team? Our Code sales team is ready to point you to the best reseller to handle your needs.</p>',
            'short' => '<p><strong>The Code Reader™ 4300 (CR4300) </strong>This product has been discontinued. If you have any questions please <a href="https://www.codecorp.com/code-support/">contact us for support.</a></p><p>As business applications go mobile, various solutions have come to market to equip these mobile devices with barcode reading capabilities. The CR4300, however, is revolutionizing how mobile devices become enterprise-grade barcode readers.</p>',
