            103 => 
            array (
                'id' => 104,
                'name' => 'Mobile Lite SDK',
            'description' => '<p>There is a lot of barcode scanning software available, including open-source and free API’s, but none of it comes with the industry experience built into CortexDecoder. Let our experience and industry-proven decoding algorithms help you confidently develop your projects and applications and deliver your competitive advantage.</p><h4>CortexDecoder Mobile Lite software features:</h4><ul><li><strong>Scanning of all 1D, PDF417, and QR barcodes</strong></li><li><strong>Easy-to-Use SDK for fast integration into consumer-facing applications</strong></li><li><strong>Support for all mobile operating systems</strong></li><li><strong>Easy integration with apps for Android, iOS, and Windows Mobile devices</strong></li><li><strong>Comprehensive support from barcode industry experts</strong></li></ul><p><i><strong>CortexDecoder Mobile Lite</strong></i> enables smartphones like the Apple iPhone and Samsung Galaxy to read barcodes like a purpose-built barcode reader. Zero-miss barcode scanning. Every scan – every time.</p><p><strong>Mobility &amp; Soft-scanning is on the Rise</strong></p><p>Through the years we’ve seen the barcode scanning industry evolve; from laser scanners to image scanners, and from 1D barcodes to complex 2D barcodes and more.&nbsp;</p><p>The software technology required to read and interpret the dozens of barcode symbologies has also evolved. At the forefront of both the hardware and software tech evolution is Code - and we are committed to continue to revolutionize scanning processes by pairing our software with the latest mobile, camera, and imaging technologies for even greater efficiency gains.</p><p><i>If a mobile SDK isn’t right for your project, check out our advanced CortexDecoder Embedded OEM software.&nbsp;</i></p><h4>Technical Specifications:&nbsp;</h4><p><strong>Symbologies Supported:</strong></p><ul><li>Codabar, Code 39, Code 93, Code 128, Interleaved 2 of 5, GS1 DataBar (RSS), UPC/EAN/JAN, PDF417, MicroPDF417, QR Code, MicroQR Code, QR Code Model 1</li></ul><p><strong>Minimum Recommended Image Resolution:</strong></p><ul><li>1 megapixel</li></ul><p><strong>O/S Support:</strong></p><ul><li>Android 4.4 and higher, iOS 8 and higher, Windows 10 Mobile</li></ul>',
                'short' => '<p>This software development kit provides developers and software engineers the most common barcode decoding algorithms for building solutions or apps with a consumer-facing purpose and experience. CortexDecoder provides consistent, high-speed, zero-miss barcode reading from any smartphone with a camera, leading to the best customer satisfaction and brand experience for your project. The Mobile Lite SDK has flexible licensing and integration support by Code Professional Services.</p>',
